<img src="/assets/nullstellenfont_ANYA.png" alt="test" /></p>

<p>For MATH 487: Algebraic Geometry at Williams College, taught by Ralph Morrison, Ben Logsdon and I created a font
out of affine varieties, called Nullstellenfont. Our <a href="/404">article</a> about it was published in the April 2020
edition of <a href="https://www.maa.org/press/periodicals/math-horizons">Math Horizons</a>.  We also created code to convert a string of text to an affine variety and
compute the defining equation. You can see an example <a href="/assets/anya-nullstellenfont.pdf">here</a>. You can
also <a href="https://sites.google.com/williams.edu/nullstellenfont/">make your own text</a> or check out the <a href="https://github.com/bclogsdon/nullstellenfont">code</a>.</p>

